<item>
            <title>[JCR-2418] Read permission on parent node required to access an item&apos;s definition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2418</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>If a session is granted all permissions on a given item B but lacks permission to read it&amp;#39;s parent node A an attempt to&lt;br/&gt;
access the definition of B by means of Node.getDefinition or Property.getDefinition will fail with AccessDeniedException.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Similarly, the same session will not be able to modify that item B - e.g. add a child node in case it was a node - since implementation e.g. checks of that&lt;br/&gt;
item B isn&amp;#39;t protected, which is determined by looking at the definition.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
My feeling is, that the item definition should be accessible even if the parent node cannot be read.</description>
